  "bio_raw": "Ms. Shaheen Ara has 16 years’ experience in teaching literature and language to undergraduate students at BRAC University, Presidency University & ULAB. She also taught BRAC employees at BRAC Center and designed new English language courses at both BRAC & ULAB. Ms. Ara is currently working at ULAB’s Center for Language Studies (CLS) as Assistant Professor, engaged in teaching and designing English language courses. Apart from teaching she was also an Advisor to ULAB Shangskriti Shangsad for three years and currently is responsible for organizing all cultural events at CLS.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "English for Academic Purposes (EAP), Teaching English Through Literature, Teaching English to Young Learners( TEYL)"
  ],
